7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Ghost Wolf
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: Burn the blossoms to peer into the spirit world. But beware of what you might see.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: {name}? Are you speaking to the spirits?

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: I see the spirits have entrusted you with a task. They chose wisely.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Ghost Wolf
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: Find my packmates. They can still be freed from their bonds.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Ghost Wolf
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: Thank you, shaman. I am in your debt.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Ghost Wolf
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: The ogres' necromancy has ravaged the spirit world.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Ghost Wolf
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: My pack and I will always be with you. Call upon us when you are in need.

7CI6d1UlBr.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
7CI6d1UlBr.Text: I remember when Shuja first communed with the spirit world. You will make a fine shaman, {name}.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: They're bringing a dragon back from the dead?! Is it too late for us to run?

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
CfyZNTgLri.Text: We do not run when our people need us! Find us a way through all of those undead.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Hey, you say jump, I provide the rocket boots. How about... a giant boar?

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Whatever you do, make it quick. My daughter's life is at stake.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Well, I promised a giant boar. Now we just gotta deliver.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Huh. That ain't right. Let's see... just gotta... there! Try it now.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Oh ho! Who needs a giant boar when we can do THAT? Here, try it again.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Now that's what I'm talking about! Let's get back to Grimaxe.

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: When you blow up those zombies, remember that my proprietary invention made it happen!

CfyZNTgLri.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
CfyZNTgLri.Text: Hey, uh... remember that little talk we had about liability? Looks like that rig is about to... explode.

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: I will join Bo farther north, where the harpies roost. Meet me there.

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Bo
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: They seem to have captured a Forsaken prisoner for their ritual.

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: I'll cut a path straight through these harpies.

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Herbert Gloomburst
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: A shame I must break such a fascinating spell. Keep the harpies away from me!

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Bo
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: I've got your back! Let us strike them down!

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: You do not fight alone! Lok-tar ogar!

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Bo
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: Something big is coming this way!

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: Then we slay it together. For the Horde!

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Herbert Gloomburst
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: I'm free! Hahaha! Ahem. Let's make ourselves scarce, shall we?

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: Well fought. We are one step closer to crushing those pitiful ogres.

cQCsEM7nDS.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
cQCsEM7nDS.Text: Recruit, we push forward! The rest of you, hold this position.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Warchief, this is the recruit I spoke of.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Lady Sylvanas Windrunner
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: It seems you have an eye for talent, Warlord Grimaxe.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Lady Sylvanas Windrunner
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Your skills come highly recommended, {name}. I will make use of them.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Lady Sylvanas Windrunner
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: To ensure our victory over the Alliance, the Horde must add strength to its ranks.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Lady Sylvanas Windrunner
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Nathanos, brief our new arrival on the mission at hand.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Nathanos Blightcaller
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Of course, my queen. We will not disappoint you.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Much glory awaits you on the battlefield, {name}.

eu0OPVZ4AJ.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
eu0OPVZ4AJ.Text: Fight with honor and always remember your training. Lok-tar ogar!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Let's move. I'll keep the ogres focused on me while you strike them down!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: We've slain almost all of them! Keep fighting!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: All this necrotic energy... the ritual must nearly be complete!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: That's one of Gor'groth's bodyguards. What's our plan of attack?

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: {name}, you strike first. I'll charge in after you. Let none stand in our way!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Tunk
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Me gonna smash, you no stop ritual!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: I'll draw his attention. Shuja, heal our wounds!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: As you command! Lok-tar!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Tunk
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Me never... see Gor'groth... win...

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Keep moving! Gor'groth must be close.

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Gor'groth! Prepare to join your precious dragon in death!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Gor'groth
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Puny vermin! You will not stop the ritual! Not after all we have done!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Gor'groth
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Ravnyr will destroy you all!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Strike now! For the Horde!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Gor'groth
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: We... will be... the final sacrifice!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: He's completing the ritual!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Did we... stop him?

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Ravnyr
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Foolish ogre! You have given me nowhere near enough power!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Lok-tar ogar! Victory or death!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Ravnyr
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Pathetic mortals. Your deaths will nourish me!

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: Hah! The ogres and their dragon lie dead at our feet, and the skies shine clear upon our victory.

fSRH3U1ZBI.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
fSRH3U1ZBI.Text: {name}, let me know when you're ready to leave this place. We must find a way back to Orgrimmar.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Lana Jordan
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Let's see if we can find one of those rituals.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Lana Jordan
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: A dark pit and darker magic. I think we found the ritual.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Lana Jordan
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: You're the only hope those survivors have left. No pressure.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Won'sa
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: And make sure ya be stoppin' dat ritual!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: A rescue party! Earth Mother, guide their path!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Hrun the Exiled
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: I will harvest your life force... and then those who sealed me in here shall burn!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Hrun the Exiled
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: You will be kindling for the flame!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Hrun the Exiled
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: If... I die... so... do you!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Thank you, friend. I will bear us to safety. Hop on!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: An'she, watch over and protect us!

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Dark magic has brought ruin to this place.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Lana Jordan
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Oh good, you made it out.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Won'sa
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Ya did good savin' da survivors an' killin' da spiders.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Those spiders had their rightful home destroyed. They deserved better.

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Won'sa
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Well if ya be puttin' it dat way...

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Lana Jordan
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: You have a problem with spiders, Won'sa?

GB1QNwU4nt.Author: Won'sa
GB1QNwU4nt.Text: Ya seen da spiders we trolls be dealin' wit', ya not be a fan of dem either.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Recruit. Quilboar pose a far greater threat than murlocs. You must be ready to face them in battle.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Your next lesson begins now!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good. Use Lightning Bolt to strike at your enemy when they're far away from you.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Fine work. Use Primal Strike when you're in melee range of your target!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Primal Strike instead of Lightning Bolt when your opponent is upon you!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Well done, now let's try using Lightning Bolt again. Brace yourself!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Again! Keep using Primal Strike when fighting face to face.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use your distance to your advantage. Strike your enemy with Lightning Bolt!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Shadow Word: Pain at the start of combat. It damages your foes over time.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good! Use Smite while Shadow Word: Pain deals damage. I'll tell you when to use Shadow Word: Pain again.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Like that, one more time! A priest can wear down their opponents with proper use of Shadow Word: Pain.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Shadow Word: Pain is fading! Cast it again!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You used Shadow Word: Pain too soon. You'll do more damage if you use it when it has almost expired.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Fine work, now do it again! Shadow Word: Pain will continue to damage your opponent while you assault them with Smite.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Frostbolt slows your enemy's movements. Keep casting it until they get close to you.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Keep using Frostbolt to hold your opponent at bay!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Stay away from your foe and hit them with Frostbolt!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Fire Blast takes no time to cast. Use it when your foe is already upon you.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good! Fire Blast's instant cast makes it perfect to use in melee range. Let's practice this again!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You can cast Fire Blast instantly, making it the best option when your foe is close to you.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Moonfire at the start of your combat. It will damage your foe over time.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Fine work. Keep using Wrath while Moonfire deals damage. I'll tell you when to use Moonfire again.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Moonfire will damage your opponent over time. Use Wrath while your foe is affected by it.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Moonfire is wearing off, cast it again!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You used Moonfire too soon. You'll do more damage if you use it when it has almost expired.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good, one more time. Moonfire and Wrath will help you strike down the quilboar.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Normal attacks won't do much on their own. Use Crusader Strike!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Holy Power burns within you! Use Shield of the Righteous now!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Crusader Strike increases your Holy Power. You'll need it to use more powerful abilities!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Again! Keep using Crusader Strike to build up your Holy Power!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good! A skilled Paladin builds up Holy Power quickly, and then uses it to damage their enemies.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You have enough Holy Power to use Shield of the Righteous!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Well fought! You're out of Holy Power, so use Crusader Strike to generate more!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Not bad, recruit. Keep using Crusader Strike to gain Holy Power.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You have enough Holy Power to end this! Use Shield of the Righteous!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Sinister Strike builds up your combo points. Use Eviscerate when you have at least three built up!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Sinister Strike as often as you can to gain combo points!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Good! Eviscerate deals more damage with every combo point. Use it again, but this time with four combo points!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You have at least three combo points! Use Eviscerate now!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Normal attacks won't do much on their own. Use Sinister Strike!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You have at least four combo points! Time to use Eviscerate!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Well done. Eviscerate spends all of your combo points. Use all five with your next Eviscerate!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Not bad, but Eviscerate is much more powerful when you have more combo points. Try again!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Focus on getting five combo points before you try using Eviscerate.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You're at five combo points. Use Eviscerate to finish this!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Corruption at the start of combat. It deals damage to your foe over time.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Again! A warlock can do devastating damage with proper use of Corruption.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Corruption will damage your opponent over time.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Corruption is wearing off, cast it again!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You used Corruption too soon. You'll do more damage if you use it when it has almost expired.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Use Charge to start the battle. Show your foe the fury of the Horde!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: A warrior should always Charge into combat. It gives you the Rage you need to use more abilities.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Slam will spend some of your Rage to deal damage. You can Slam as long as you have enough Rage!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Charge towards me!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Don't rely on your normal attacks. Use Slam!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Charge at me again to get within striking distance! Always begin combat with a Charge.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Well fought! Charge will build your Rage and damage your enemies. Always use it to start a fight.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: One more time. Charge!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: You've got promise. Let's do it one more time before you face the quilboar.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Show me your ranged combat again. It will benefit you against foes who have to close the distance.

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Remember that you can deal plenty of damage as your foe runs towards you!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Overwhelm the enemy with melee attacks. You're learning fast!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Enough! You're ready to fight the quilboar. Now we rescue our brethren!

gDoZ5iqxjG.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
gDoZ5iqxjG.Text: Your spells can be used at range. Cast them to assault your enemies and land the first strike!

GdzsDWwzVk.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
GdzsDWwzVk.Text: She's my daughter. Nothing could keep me from her.

GdzsDWwzVk.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
GdzsDWwzVk.Text: And as a soldier of the Horde, she knows we leave no one behind.

GdzsDWwzVk.Author: Won'sa
GdzsDWwzVk.Text: We got ambushed... by da quilboar...

GdzsDWwzVk.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
GdzsDWwzVk.Text: Eat first. I won't let you starve to death.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
hvzbXBQACd.Text: Look sharp, {name}! We're almost to the island.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
hvzbXBQACd.Text: We need to be ready for anything. Show me your skill in combat.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
hvzbXBQACd.Text: Fine work. Next, we... rain? Our shaman said the skies would be clear.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
hvzbXBQACd.Text: Throg will spar with you for now. I must speak to the crew about the rain.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Grunt Throg
hvzbXBQACd.Text: I'll take my position. Strike first, and strike hard!

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Grunt Throg
hvzbXBQACd.Text: Never run from your foe! Victory or death!

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Grunt Throg
hvzbXBQACd.Text: I concede! Your strength will see our mission through.

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Grunt Throg
hvzbXBQACd.Text: Warlord! This storm will soon overwhelm us!

hvzbXBQACd.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
hvzbXBQACd.Text: {name}! You survived! We need to regroup at once.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: I must report to the warchief. Cork will show you around the city for now.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Bet ya that guard can point us to the stables.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Welcome to the big time, {name}. You're in Orgrimmar now. Anyone who's anyone does business here.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Yeah, it's hot and dusty, and the orcs ain't always hospitable... but it's got charm, huh?

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: See, the thing about Orgrimmar is that it's a place we can call our own. And that means a lot to people.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: If the goons in the Alliance had their way, we wouldn't even have that much.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Let's visit a trainer to learn about specializing your skills!

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Come on, let's hit the Wyvern's Tail. You can buy me a drink!

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: {name}, I bring word from the warchief!

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: The warchief awaits you in Grommash Hold.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: I always knew you'd make a name for yourself, {name}.

nU6m6LxjTi.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
nU6m6LxjTi.Text: Watch your back out there, will ya? And put in a good word with the warchief for me!

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: We'll head north to see what the others have found. Won'sa, rest and regain your strength before joining us.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Won'sa
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: I be seein' ya soon, den. Ya daughter be right ta count on ya.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: The Horde never abandons its soldiers. I will not abandon her.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Mithdran Dawntracker
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: Good, you're here. The quilboar are conducting some foul ritual...

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Mithdran Dawntracker
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: I will teach you the basics as fast as I can. Do pay attention.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Mithdran Dawntracker
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: That shall have to do for now. Find a beast and tame it.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: We move, now. Those monsters have my daughter.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Mithdran Dawntracker
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: Shuja? I saw no sign of her. Perhaps she evaded capture.

NZTbW4kkHF.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
NZTbW4kkHF.Text: One can hope. She rarely acts with such caution.

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: And that's why I always bet on the Horde! Let's scram!

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: You must be Warlord Breka! Shuja's mother! She always said you'd save our hides.

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: We're not safe just yet. Where are the others?

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: No idea... but I've got a way to find out!

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: This here's a tiny version of the Choppy Booster Mark 5. Just let me enlarge it...

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: Okay, might have overdone it a bit. Hold on...

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: Perfect! It ain't pretty, but it gets the job done.

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: Can you hear me, {name}? Looks like the camera is workin' like a charm!

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: If it has a camera then why does someone need to be up there?

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: I need a back up plan in case your recruit gets dropped like a rock.

OY4nHlkRzt.Author: Cork Fizzlepop
OY4nHlkRzt.Text: Uhh, is this thing still on? Hey pal, you accepted all liability by agreeing to this!

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Herbert Gloomburst
rybCOGj7A4.Text: A willing test subject! Such a rare find.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Good. Now act like an ogre and get us inside.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Don't speak. Just smile and wave. The dumber you look, the better.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Ogre Brute
rybCOGj7A4.Text: More sacrifices! Go to cooking pit, wave at Gor'groth. Show what you got!

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Keep moving. See if we can learn anything about the ritual.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Gor'groth
rybCOGj7A4.Text: What do we have here... all the sacrifices we thought we lost!

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Gor'groth
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Take them to the back. We'll seal them with the ward stones like we did their leader.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Gor'groth
rybCOGj7A4.Text: It is time to complete the ritual atop the citadel. Then all will bow before us!

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Warlord Thunderwalker! Quickly, help me destroy these seals!

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Raw strength won't be enough. We need to end the spell.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
rybCOGj7A4.Text: Gor'groth spoke of ward stones. Find them and use them to free the warlord.

rybCOGj7A4.Author: Warlord Mulgrin Thunderwalker
rybCOGj7A4.Text: You have my thanks... but we must still end the ogres' ritual!

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: Dispel the foul magic that binds me here.

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: I attempted to bring an end to these rituals...

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: But the ogres ensnared me... drained my power...

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: Free me, so I might recover... and pass some of my power to you.

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: The spell is weakening... the Light returns to me!

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: Ahh, freedom! You have my gratitude.

THfHRrEHnR.Author: Lightspawn
THfHRrEHnR.Text: Accept my blessing, and end the necromancy that plagues this island.

W3yKJotsGS.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
W3yKJotsGS.Text: Recover our supplies, but don't fight too many murlocs at once. They're dangerous in packs.

W3yKJotsGS.Author: Lana Jordan
W3yKJotsGS.Text: Quite the storm. Probably hit the first boat, too.

W3yKJotsGS.Author: Mithdran Dawntracker
W3yKJotsGS.Text: Mark my words, that storm was unnatural.

W3yKJotsGS.Author: Bo
W3yKJotsGS.Text: My thanks. We'll find the expedition yet.

W3yKJotsGS.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
W3yKJotsGS.Text: You three, search for more survivors. {name}, you and I will push forward.

x8ghyDZyie.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
x8ghyDZyie.Text: Hang on, Shuja! Recruit, with me! Lok-tar ogar!

x8ghyDZyie.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
x8ghyDZyie.Text: Wretched ogre. Let's check on Shuja.

x8ghyDZyie.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
x8ghyDZyie.Text: Mother... I tried to stop the ogres on my own. But I failed. My strength was not enough.

x8ghyDZyie.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
x8ghyDZyie.Text: Shuja, the Horde is strong not when we fight alone, but when we stand united. Now, tell me what's happened here.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: Horde reinforcements! I knew they would find us.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Bruk'tor
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: Blood and thunder, soldiers! We've been trying to push our way past the storm.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: Mount a wyvern and fly home to Orgrimmar. Glory awaits us.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Herbert Gloomburst
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: To think those brutes could wield such magic. If only I had more time to study it!

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Crenna Earth-Daughter
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: I am glad that you do not. This island must be allowed to heal.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Shuja Grimaxe
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: Look, {name}, on the horizon. One of our gunships!

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: An impressive display of the Horde's strength. Those ogres would do well to run and hide.

XmOB4MgE6o.Author: Warlord Breka Grimaxe
XmOB4MgE6o.Text: Come, recruits. It is time we return to our home.
